06425nam a22010095i 9783035610840DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20172017sz     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)993106944  a97830356108407 a10.1515/97830356108402doi  a(DE-B1597)474909  a(OCoLC)992489787  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a70022300aSUPERSUIT :bPoetic Interventions in Urban Spaces /ced. by Daniel Aschwanden, Michael Wallraff. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (112 p.) :bzahlr. farb. Abb.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aEdition Angewandte00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tEditors’ Foreword -- tPerson in the Crowd: Stories of Supersuit -- tThe City a Stage -- tPerforming the City, Performing the Space: Touching the Invisible -- tFirst Test Setup -- tSecond Test Setup -- tTo Suit the Super -- tDevelopment of The Structure -- tDynamics in Equilibrium -- tPerformance Diary -- t1. Vienna -- tProjection as Mirror of the City -- t2. Addis Ababa -- tCondominium in Lideta: Lawns, Castaways, and Art -- tMaking Sense of Confined Urban Realities -- tDiscussion of the Performance on Mexico Square in Addis Ababa -- t3. Wuhan -- tSupersuit & Gold Field -- tBiographies -- tProject Credits / Colophon0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie zunehmende Akkumulation von Menschen in geschichtslosen Wohnmaschinen, die Herausforderungen durch Migration und Platzmangel aktualisieren den Bedarf für ein neues Denken und Handeln in öffentlichen Räumen. SUPERSUIT ist ein interdisziplinäres Experiment an der Grenze zwischen Mensch und Raum. Er ist ein Werkzeug für poetische Interventionen in unterschiedlichen urbanen Situationen, lädt zur Partizipation ein und hinterfragt die Beziehung von Mensch, Raum und Stadt in sinnlicher Form. Als Marker öffentlichen Raumes antworten die spontan entstehenden Formen des SUPERSUIT unmittelbar auf Parameter des urbanen Kontexts. SUPERSUIT ermöglicht über performative Interventionen die Veränderung aktueller Designprozesse und die Konzeption neuer Mensch-Material-Konstellationen.  aThe increasing accumulation of people in living machines without history and the challenges presented by migration and the lack of space provoke a need for new thinking and acting in public spaces. SUPERSUIT is an interdisciplinary experiment at the demarcation between people and space. It is a tool for poetic interventions in a range of different urban situations that invites participation and queries the relationship between people, space and city in terms of sense perception. As a marker of public space, the spontaneously arising forms of SUPERSUIT respond directly to the parameters of urban context. Using the means of ‘performative interventions’ SUPERSUIT facilitates a change in current design processes and the conceptualizing of new people/material constellations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planning. 0aPerformance artzAustriazVienna. 4aMensch-Raum-Symbiose. 4aPerformance /Öffentlicher Raum. 4aPerformative Architektur. 4aRaumexperiment. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aAschwanden, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAschwanden, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAuersperg, Manora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBo, Mu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeribew, Berhanu Ashagrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelderer, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmann, Arne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r